        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 21 at 7:52AM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 752 AM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Sand Bed, or 7 miles
east of Perry, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Perry, Cochran, Hawkinsville, Hayneville, Browndale, Meadowdale,
Empire, Houston Lake, Mobley Crossing, Grove Park, Royal, Ocmulgee
Public Fishing Area, Moss Oak, Paulk, Pulaski State Prison, Porter,
Kathleen, Coley Station, Sand Bed, and Grovania.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
